<img width="750" height="750" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/another-week-mac-mgg996.jpg?fit=750%2C750&amp;ssl=1" class="webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image" alt="Another Week, Another New Mac – Mac Geek Gab 996 episode image" style="display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;max-width: 100%;" link_thumbnail="" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/another-week-mac-mgg996.jpg?w=3000&amp;ssl=1 3000w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/another-week-mac-mgg996.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/another-week-mac-mgg996.jpg?resize=1024%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/another-week-mac-mgg996.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/another-week-mac-mgg996.jpg?resize=768%2C768&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/another-week-mac-mgg996.jpg?resize=1536%2C1536&amp;ssl=1 1536w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/another-week-mac-mgg996.jpg?resize=2048%2C2048&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/another-week-mac-mgg996.jpg?resize=600%2C600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/another-week-mac-mgg996.jpg?resize=230%2C230&amp;ssl=1 230w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/another-week-mac-mgg996.jpg?resize=160%2C160&amp;ssl=1 160w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/another-week-mac-mgg996.jpg?resize=50%2C50&amp;ssl=1 50w, https://i0.wp.com/www.macgeekgab.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/another-week-mac-mgg996.jpg?w=2250&amp;ssl=1 2250w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px" /><p>From unlocking the secrets of the command key in Spotlight to the ins and outs of Siri commands for Apple TVs, Pilot Pete and Dave Hamilton leave no stone unturned. They navigate the intricacies of the Synology interface, dive deep into the custom domains world of iCloud Plus, and address security concerns by emphasizing the mantra, &#8220;Don&#8217;t Get Caught&#8221;, when using the same rescue email for custom domain emails and Apple IDs.</p>
<p>As your two favorite geeks pivot towards iPads and Finder&#8217;s capabilities on macOS, the conversation illuminates the nuances of SMB vs. AFP, iPhone emergency services, and the treasure trove of iPhone Life&#8217;s tip of the day newsletter. They don&#8217;t stop there; discussions range from exploring Mac backup options, unraveling Mac storage space mysteries, password and privacy necessities, to a meticulous analysis of USB-C and Thunderbolt cable compatibilities.</p>
<p>However, it&#8217;s not all software and cables. Dave and Pete touch on the perils and perks of Apple Silicon devices, while also diving into some engaging hardware conversations, including troubleshooting an iMac backlight issue and debating the pros and cons of computer upgrades. They then veer into the entertainment sector, discussing the sonic brilliance of a portable JBL speaker and sharing a light-hearted tale of a car stereo gone wrong. Wrapping up, they serve a sprinkle of trivia about the Atlanta airport and hint at what&#8217;s to come. Press play, don&#8217;t get caught, end enjoy learning at least five new things!</p>
